        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 5:54PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 553 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 16
miles east of Anderson, or 7 miles southeast of Williamston, moving
south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Honea Path, Princeton, and Fork Shoals.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
